5|$|The Dutch {{released}} {{reports of}} <b>German</b> <b>soldiers</b> in disguise {{to the international}} news agencies. This caused a fifth column scare, especially in Belgium and France. However, unlike the situation later on in those two countries, in the Netherlands there was no mass exodus of civilian refugees, clogging the roads. Generally <b>German</b> <b>soldiers</b> behaved in a civilised manner towards the Dutch population, forming neat queues at the shops to buy goods rationed in Germany, such as chocolate.|$|E
