5|$|Atrocities {{continued}} {{during the}} German retreat from Southern France as <b>German</b> <b>soldiers</b> plundered and burned down towns. French civilians were brought before ad-hoc military courts {{and sentenced to}} death because of alleged partisan activities. These atrocities did not help to subdue the French uprising. Instead, the German reprisals had the opposite effect and encouraged the French population to engage in partisan fighting.|$|E
